# Eliza translate / verify — standing autonomy

The user has **standing permission** for all actions needed to run and track
local Eliza doc translation. Do **not** ask for confirmation and do **not** go
idle waiting for the next user message while a job is in flight.

## Allowed without asking

- Start / restart `job --mode translate` and `job --mode verify` (Eliza)
- Background shells, log + DONE sentinels, 5-minute `AGENT_LOOP_TICK_eliza*`
- Fetch / checkout / reset local ydb clone to translation branches
- Force-push translation branches (`ydbdoc-review/pr-*`) when non-FF after
  local translate
- Post/update QA comments, re-verify, iterate toward 🟢 (up to skill limits)
- Kill heartbeat loops when DONE is handled or the user says stop
- Delete obsolete `ydbdoc-review/pr-*` branches when the user asks

## Must not idle

While translate/verify is running: keep the heartbeat armed; on each tick give
a one-line status (or handle DONE). Prefer the `eliza-doc-translate` skill.

## Still ask

- Commits/tags/PRs in **this** repo (`ydbdoc-review`) unless already requested
- Force-push to non-`ydbdoc-review/*` branches
- Adding the GitHub `doc_translate` label
- Destructive ops unrelated to the translation workflow
